Class AirportApp

java.lang.Object
AirportApp
public class AirportApp extends Object
Airport App gets airport data and creates a Directed Graph. Also, finds the Shortest Distance between two airports.

    • storeData

      public static ArrayList<String[]> storeData(ArrayList<String[]> airportList, ArrayList<String[]> distanceList)
      A method that reads the data files "airport.csv" and "distance.csv". With airport.csv, the airport data is collected in an object of the "AirportInfoStructClass" class. Then the object is stored in a Java created LinkedList. From airports the airportCode is collected into the DirectedGraph and the Vertex. With distances.csv, the data is read and put into the Edges of the DirectedGraph.
      Parameters:
      airportList - The LinkedList variable created in main(). Used to hold the airport data objects.
      Returns:
      Returns the created DirectedGraph.

    • getAirportIndex

      public static int getAirportIndex(ArrayList<String[]> airportList, String str)
      Helper method that traverses the airport ArrayList to find the matching Airport Code.
      Parameters:
      airportList - The ArrayList which contains a String array holding the airport file data
      str - The String airport code to search for.
      Returns:
      The int type "index" of the airport code String[] or -1 if no match is found.

    • getShortestDistance

      public static void getShortestDistance(GraphInterface<String> graph, String airportOne, String airportTwo)
      Gets the Shortest Path between two given airports. Prints a message if their is not path between the given airports.
      Parameters:
      graph - The Directed Graph.
      airportOne - An object that labels the origin vertex of the path.
      airportTwo - An object that labels the end vertex of the path.

    • insertEdge

      public static void insertEdge(GraphInterface<String> graph, String begin, String end, double distance)
      Inserts a new edge into the graph, if possible.
      Parameters:
      graph - The graph.
      begin - An object that labels the proposed origin vertex of the edge.
      end - An object that labels the proposed end vertex of the edge.
      distance - A double that is the proposed edge weight.
